4 things you needs to know if you are trying to snatch your waist the natural way. 

1. You should not be training abs every day!  Your core/ab area is a muscle and just like the other muscles in your body ( that you don’t train every day) you don’t need to train abs every day. They need a little rest and time to recover like every other muscle. 

2. Doing 100+ #abexercises is a whole waist of time if your #diet is 🗑️. 

3. Quality is ALWAYS better than quantity! Doing 100+ reps is a waste of time if only 3 of the reps were actually good reps. Focus on perfecting form! 

4. You can’t spot treat: “ I wanna loose my gut and keep my butt” ain’t about to happen! When the fat comes off it’s coming from EVERYWHERE… GUT and BUTT. 😉

📝Tips For Beginners 📝

1. Start small: If you’re just beginning your journey start small and grow. Pick 3-5 days during the week where you are going to commit to being active/working out for 20-30 minutes. Do this for 2 weeks then increase days and workout times. 

2. Do exercises and workouts you like to do: IG has a slew of great workouts and exercises, HOWEVER when you’re starting, pick exercises and workouts you actually LIKE to do. This will help you stay consistent. 

3. Warm up and cool down : 5 minutes before and after. Working out on muscles that haven’t been warmed up can lead to injury. Same with cooling down. 

4. Life is about balance.Live by the 80/20 rule: No carbs, no sugar ,no alcohol 🙄 that all sounds cute, but it’s not realistic and is not sustainable.  Enjoy a little sugar, a mixed drink and a piece of bread- all in moderation 😉

5. Celebrate Yourself: This health and wellness journey is not easy, so celebrate even the small wins!!! 🎉🥳

Now go be GREAT! 💪🏽

You’ve been hitting the gym but haven’t seen the results you were expecting. There could be a few reasons for this: 
You’re not prioritizing nutrition: Skipping meals,  not eating the right foods, eating too much or not enough are all hindering you from seeing the results you want in the gym. You cannot outwork a bad diet. 

You’re not prioritizing rest:  Did you know when you work out you are breaking down muscle fibers? These fibers help you build muscle and come back stronger- when given enough time to repair themselves. So, yes, it is okay to take a rest day or two. 

You have unrealistic goals: You want to lose or gain weight, but you’re not consuming the rights foods or doing the right workouts.  Your goals don’t match what you are currently doing. 

Your workouts are inconsistent:  Want to see results in the gym you need to hit the gym more than once or twice a week. For weight loss/gain results, I would recommend getting up and getting active at least 5 times a week. 

#weightloss #weightlossjourney #weightlosstips #exercisemotivation #workoutroutine #athomeworkouts #workouttips #fitnesstips

Take your fitness routine to the next level with these incredible compound exercises. Whether you prefer working out in a gym or at home, these versatile moves will help you build strength and tone your muscles.

What’s a compound exercise: 
~A movement that uses multiple muscle groups at one time. 

Benefits of compound exercises: 
~Adding compound exercises to your workout routine can help you burn more calories, increase, improve movement, build core strength and can save you time ⏱️

The workout 
~ I like to pick 4-5 compound exercises per workout and complete each move for 60 seconds. With a 30 second resting break after reach move. Repeating each move 3-4 times.

💪🏽December Challenge💪🏽

~12k Steps a day: I have consistently hi 8k-10k step a day for the last few years and wanted to challenge myself by upping my daily step goal. 8k-10k is recommended for weight loss and what I typically recommend for my clients. 

2-3 servings of fruits and veggie: these foods are very nutrient-dense and are also low in calories! 

4-5 bottles of water: no calories, a great detox and helps control appetite. 

Zumba 2x a week: I’m a Zumba instructor, so these two days a week are a staple in my week and an easy and fun way for me to get in my cardio for the week. 

Weight Lifting 3x a week: Strength training builds lean muscle and gives you the “toned” look. 

180 grams of lean protein: In times of caloric restriction ( eating less calories) protein helps preserves lean body mass. 

Pizza once a week- Restrictively eating is a NO for me. I like to take a break at least once a week and eat something I love!

4 Simple Tips To Help You  Lose Weight In 2024 

You need to focus on Nutrition, Consistency, Actually Doing The Work with a side of activity.

#TRUTH Let’s talk about what you really need to be focusing on if you want to lose weight in 2024! 

If you don’t have an understanding of these things, I don’t care what program you do or who you go to you WILL NOT see results! 

Nutrition 🥗🍓
- [ ] Eating in a calorie deficit
- [ ] Eating the right foods 
- [ ] Drinking plenty of water 

Activity 🚶‍♀️ 
- [ ]  Getting in 20-30+ minutes of physical activity  4-6 times a week. 
- [ ] Increasing your movement throughout the day to burn extra calories! 

Consistency 🕰️ 
-[ ]YOU HAVE TO BE CONSISTENT -With your workouts and your nutrition. #TRUTH “eating good” and working out for 1-2 weeks, isn’t going to yield the results you want. You have to KEEP showing up! Change happens over time, not overnight. 

Doing the work 💪🏽
- [ ] The only way ANY PROGRAM is going to work is if YOU DO THE WORK!! The secret to this whole fitness thing is YOU!!!!!!! Nobody can do the work for you.

January  #Fitness Challenge 
Let’s start January right with an easy to follow challenge. 

💥8k-10k steps a day: Did you know the average person only gets between 2k-4k steps a day? Increasing your daily steps can help you lose some unwanted calories. 

💥3 Veggies/Fruit a day: We all know the kitchen is the most important part of any diet and fruits and veggies are a BIG part of that! Low in cals, high in fiber and they are very nutrient dense. 

💥5-6 Bottles of Water: No Calories, No Sugar, No Carbs, Natural Detox and helps with cravings. 
Weight Lifting 3-4x a week: Want that “toned” look? Well, that “toned” look is actually muscle. So, make sure you grab some weights and lift. 

💥Cardio 2-3x a week: at least 20-30 minutes. You can hit the treadmill, take a walk or do a dance class like Zumba. 

💥No Alcohol : Empty Calories that we are going to put to the side for 31 days.
